I created a Digital Literacy Awareness infographic using Canva. The platform provided a wide
range of templates, icons, and design features that helped me organize and present information
in a clear and visually appealing format. I focused on making the infographic simple,
informative, and easy for students to understand at a glance.

My infographic covers three key areas: digital literacy, safe internet practices, most used digital
and maintaining a professional online presence. I described digital literacy as the ability to use
digital technologies effectively, responsibly, and ethically in everyday life. Under safe internet
practices, I included important points such as using strong and unique passwords, avoiding
suspicious links, protecting personal information, and being aware of online scams and cyber
threats. I also emphasized the importance of maintaining a professional online presence by
using respectful communication, following proper email etiquette, and being careful about the
content shared on social media platforms.

While designing the infographic, I found it interesting how the use of colors, icons, and layout
can improve understanding and make information more engaging for viewers. One challenge I
faced was selecting the most relevant information and organizing it in a neat and balanced way
without overcrowding the design. This task helped me improve my understanding of digital
literacy concepts while also enhancing my creativity, design thinking, and communication
skills
